I was lonely, and dropped me a word;
And I answered with one or two words more;
Then he said that he'd come to my house next day,
But he never came any more.

He had been in love before, but it ended sadly,
For his sweetheart went away;
So when he saw me so sad and forlorn,
His heart began to melt like clay.

When we met at last, how happy we were!
We talked about our hopes and fears;
Till the sun set down behind the hill,
And the moon rose up out of the tears.

The stars looked on us as they shone brightly,
As if they knew what we meant;
They seemed to say, "You are not alone now,"
While their light fell upon us bent.

Our hearts beat fast, and our eyes grew dim,
With the hope that we felt within;
And then he kissed me, and I loved him,
And we promised each other again.

Together, hand in hand, we walk around the path today,

Suddenly, like a flash, he sees the red car, and he’s off in a daze,

My head’s spinning ‘round and ‘round, he doesn’t see me, he’s gone;

Saying good-bye, I am alone, sitting and sobbing on the ground.

How could he leave me in this place?

And why did he have to go so fast?

And now what shall I do? This is simply not my world;

For I am human and have feelings and so it’s clear

My son will always be here, but what’s not clear, and what I can’t see;

Is where his body goes, when he’s gone so far.

I can’t go on like this, what will become of me?

No more running, I must stay put, I see now what I must do;

I’ll sit with all the pain, my sadness will be me:

While, my new journey will begin with a new friend to see;

And, I’ll walk hand in hand together, with that very special child;

That is no longer my son but has a new identity

And now we can walk together and I am whole;

My son is still here and now, for I can feel that he is so …

For that’s my new experience, that is my new beginning

And I’m learning to accept, my new and very special friend.

Thanks a lot, Mom,

